	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				VhalSera looks like a version of the Efreeti Lord in Sol B dressed in snow gear.  Single group of 54 Wizard, 45 Chanter, 51 Cleric, 51 Warrior, 45 Ranger, 54 Druid took him out with a DECENT amount of difficulty.  Most of the casters had partial if not complete resists on nukes (including Druid, Cleric, and Chanter).  However, the spell that turned the tide was Lure of Frost.  Hit for max damage every single time.  Without it, we'd be dead.  He seems to have some kind of massive HP regen because without constant nukes, his HP bar would rise in regular increments.  Exact HP regen unknown, if any.<BR>
<BR>
The key to beating this guy is mezzing the two bats that come with him.  DO NOT kill the bats first because they spawn enraged vampires in their place who are as tough to kill as VhalSera.  Need a decent amount of Wizard power to simplify the kill.  If you don't have it, you'd better have an extra healer and three extra melee to make up the difference.  I'm sure the kill is easier with additional 50+ levelers.  Still unknown if the Talisman he drops is for anything else.  Not a particularly good neck item.<BR>
<BR>
Wraithwave FeaA'mael<BR>
54th Generation Channeler of Oira Feanor<BR>
Cazic-Thule
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
